cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, so it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses weak supervision, which is a common topic in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions using random walk, which is a common technique in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
